{"type":"message","id":"647f5da2","parentId":"c6ab0a1e","timestamp":"2026-04-06T02:02:41.136Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4owea2r0x7m1_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The image shows a terminal output from a Linux system (specifically Xubuntu, based on the file paths) that displays two different things happening simultaneously:\n\n### 1. GitHub CLI Authentication\nThe first two lines are part of the **`gh auth login`** process:\n*   **\"First copy your one-time code: 9230-A291\"**: This is a security code used to link your local terminal to your GitHub account.\n*   **\"Press Enter to open github.com in your browser...\"**: The tool is waiting for user input to launch a web browser where you would enter that code.\n\n### 2. Snap Package Errors\nThe rest of the text is a series of error messages related to **Snap packages** (Ubuntu's app packaging system). These errors are occurring in the background, likely triggered because the system is trying to launch Firefox (a Snap-based browser) to complete the GitHub login.\n\n*   **Mount Namespace Errors:** The long list of `update.go:85: cannot change mount namespace...` errors typically occurs when there is a mismatch between the Snap daemon (`snapd`) and the system's current state, or when permissions are restricted. It indicates that the Snap environment is struggling to map host files into the application's isolated \"sandbox.\"\n*   **GPU Provider Error:** The final line (`Content snap command-chain for /snap/firefox... not found`) suggests a specific failure in the Firefox snap configuration, likely because a required \"content slot\" (a way for Snaps to share files, in this case for GPU drivers) is not properly connected.\n\n### Summary\nYou are **not** seeing an installation result; you are seeing a **login attempt that is failing to launch the browser.**\n\nBecause the Firefox Snap is broken on your system, it cannot open the GitHub authentication page. To fix this, you might need to run:\n`sudo snap connect firefox:gpu-2404` (or the equivalent for your version) or try restarting the `snapd` service. Alternatively, you can complete the login on another device by visiting github.com/login/device manually and entering the code `9230-A291`."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/0f6c58b9-6823-4c00-a04b-da73c6705a31.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775440961108}}
{"type":"message","id":"086200c3","parentId":"647f5da2","timestamp":"2026-04-06T02:02:46.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The image shows that `gh auth login` is running and waiting for the user to press Enter to open github.com in the browser. However, the Firefox snap is broken and can't launch the browser. \n\nThe solution is: the user can go to https://github.com/login/device on any browser and enter the code 9230-A291 to complete the authentication. They don't need to use the browser on the server.","thinkingSignature":"294a54bd7604adc7a0ce5dda4dd5b074374a61e27d192b15c382bdd4b6ef5867"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了。`gh auth login` 已经在运行，代码是 **9230-A291**。\n\n但服务器上的 Firefox (Snap) 坏了打不开浏览器。**换个方式完成授权：**\n\n1. 你在**任何设备**（电脑/手机）的浏览器打开：https://github.com/login/device\n2. 输入代码：**9230-A291**\n3. 授权完成\n\n完成后告诉我。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8630,"output":170,"cacheRead":12505,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21305,"cost":{"input":0.0025889999999999997,"output":0.000204,"cacheRead":0.0007503,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0035433}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775440961137,"responseId":"062247410aa57f57812c27acbf82aaf1"}}
