{"type":"message","id":"af09dc91","parentId":"e356df52","timestamp":"2026-04-06T03:58:47.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The service is running inside the container on port 1933, but it's not exposed to the host. The issue is the Docker port mapping. \n\nThe openclaw.json is configured to connect to `http://localhost:1933`, but since the port isn't mapped, it can't connect. \n\nI need to either:\n1. Add port mapping for 1933 when running the container\n2. Or change the openclaw config to use a different approach\n\nLet me check how the container was started and what docker-compose or docker run command is being used.","thinkingSignature":"4ff4cebee78ebd31ee537901de5be84f91065f024dd49e9c388441ee58590e0f"},{"type":"text","text":"OpenViking 容器内是通的，但 **1933 端口没映射到宿主机**。`curl localhost:1933` 失败。\n\n这就是为什么集成失败。你重装的时候端口映射丢了。\n\n**解决方案：** 需要把 1933 映射出来：\n\n```bash\ndocker stop openviking\ndocker rm openviking\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name openviking \\\n  -p 1933:1933 \\\n  -p 8020:8020 \\\n  -v /home/halei/.openviking:/data \\\n  ghcr.io/volcengine/openviking:latest\n```\n\n或者如果你用 docker-compose，贴一下你的 compose 文件，我帮你改。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33618,"output":261,"cacheRead":12505,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46384,"cost":{"input":0.0100854,"output":0.00031319999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0007503,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0111489}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775447920005,"responseId":"06226270730cb7b716c85a7c5d95d228"}}
