{"type":"message","id":"5c0b6fea","parentId":"5e4dd423","timestamp":"2026-04-06T04:12:58.304Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-06 12:12:50 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b520762d128b4c4351d58322c077]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b520762d128b4c4351d58322c077\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-06 12:12 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n先放到这我在考虑一下，你有再想想什么方案最更好一点的，GitHub又不花钱。"}],"timestamp":1775448778180}}
{"type":"message","id":"472e526f","parentId":"5c0b6fea","timestamp":"2026-04-06T04:13:15.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying to pause and think about a better backup strategy, since GitHub storage is free. Let me think about what data should be backed up and the best approach.\n\nWhat we have:\n1. OpenClaw data at `~/.openclaw/` (164MB total)\n2. OpenViking data at `~/.openviking/` (4.4MB)\n\nWhat GitHub offers:\n- Free private repos with unlimited storage (though recommended to keep under 1GB per repo)\n- Git LFS available if needed for large files\n\nLet me think about what makes sense to back up:\n\n**Should back up:**\n1. `workspace/` - Memory files, SOUL.md, MEMORY.md - CRITICAL, should always back up\n\n\n2. `openclaw.json` (redacted version) - Config\n3. `agents/` - Agent configurations\n4. `skills/` - Custom skills\n5. `cron/` - Cron jobs\n6. `identity/` - Identity config\n7. `memory/` files in workspace\n8. `lcm.db` - Chat history and sessions metadata (SQLite, could be几十MB)\n9. `sessions/*.jsonl` - Chat message logs (sensitive but important for context)\n10. OpenViking data - session context and vector DB\n\nThe issue is that raw chat logs contain sensitive information, so I need to think through how to handle that securely.\n\nI'm considering a few approaches: keeping everything in git since GitHub has generous storage, setting up git LFS for large files like SQLite databases and media, or just being selective with what gets backed up. GitHub's soft limit is around 1GB with a recommended ceiling of 5GB for free accounts, and they don't enforce strict storage limits on private repos anyway. Since the current backup is only 22MB, I have plenty of room to grow. I should recommend using git LFS for the larger components like lcm.db and media files since they're binary and not well-suited for regular git storage.\n\nI should also add the OpenViking data to the backup since it's important context, while excluding the sessions logs since they're quite large. Let me look at what's actually in those session files to understand the scope better.","thinkingSignature":"ad3b7a4163c5c0e1fa0381e4d70bdadac0e9e3a4a22da36fe3504b92347dafd7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4flxbqdxf7rp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"du -sh ~/.openclaw/sessions/ ~/.openclaw/media/ ~/.openviking/ 2>/dev/null; ls ~/.openclaw/sessions/*.jsonl 2>/dev/null | wc -l"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39,"output":524,"cacheRead":51162,"cacheWrite":696,"totalTokens":52421,"cost":{"input":0.0000117,"output":0.0006288,"cacheRead":0.0030697199999999997,"cacheWrite":0.000261,"total":0.00397122}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775448778195,"responseId":"062265ccd3993064333acaeb2f9ffa47"}}
