{"type":"message","id":"64885367","parentId":"700c73a5","timestamp":"2026-04-06T04:17:19.206Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user said \"先您看这办\" which seems like \"先您看着办\" - meaning \"up to you to decide\" or \"use your judgment.\" They want me to decide the best approach for the backup.\n\nLet me think about the optimal backup strategy given:\n1. GitHub private repo is free and has plenty of space\n2. They want comprehensive backup\n3. Security concerns about credentials\n\nMy recommendation:\n1. Set up Git LFS for large binary files (lcm.db, media, sessions, OpenViking data)\n2. Full backup everything except credentials/ and extensions/\n3. This way all data is backed up, only real secrets are excluded\n\n\n4. Now I'll update the backup script to include all the additional data sources and configure Git LFS to handle the binary files properly.","thinkingSignature":"0b712a5d0ae5d26bcaf7dc96053ad5bda59358b9e1af32f90e71a3715231c41b"},{"type":"text","text":"好，我来做全量方案，把能备份的都加上：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l1pdvppvetzy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh api repos/59330857/openclaw-backup 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E \"size|updated\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39,"output":234,"cacheRead":52897,"cacheWrite":803,"totalTokens":53973,"cost":{"input":0.0000117,"output":0.0002808,"cacheRead":0.0031738199999999995,"cacheWrite":0.000301125,"total":0.0037674449999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775449029720,"responseId":"062266c75278d95a4ae9c7e6f8752086"}}
